Pour @water{300%ml}(cold and salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting 
#lid{}. Stir in the @rice{150%grams} then bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid. Cook for 
~{10%minutes} then remove the pot from the heat. Keep covered for another 
~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its 
own steam).

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}. Halve the 
@bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel 
and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Place a #large pan{} 
over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the @turkey mince{250%grams} and pepper until the turkey is browned, 
about ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince with a #spoon{} as it cooks. Season with 
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Add garlic, @ground cumin{1%sachet} and @Mexican style spice mix{2%sachets} to 
the pan. Cook, stirring, for ~{30%secs}.

Pour in @chopped tomatoes with onion & garlic{1%pack}, beans, @chicken stock{1%sachet}, 
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{75%ml}. Bring to the boil then lower heat to medium.

Simmer until the sauce is nice and thick, about ~{6-8%minutes}. Stir often to 
prevent sticking.

> IMPORTANT: Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Loosen the sauce with a splash of water 
if necessary.

Stir in as much of the @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} as you like (use less if 
you don't like spice).

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between #bowls{}. Top with spoonfuls 
of turkey chilli. Finish with a scattering of @grated cheese{50%grams}.